The paper discusses overlearning in image-analysis and NLP models, which are typically studied in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the privacy and bias implications of overlearning, which are relevant to the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
